Abstract: This paper studies strategy related beliefs in five organizations in Hungary with substantial foreign participation. We find that one of the strongest determinants of similarity of beliefs was being a member of the functional area favored by the strategic change. The effect of being in the favored area was greater than the effect of all other individual characteristics, including nationality.&copy; 2000 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (2000) 31, 427&ndash;442
